"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-24-2024-olympics-var-drama-as-argentina-vs-morocco-match-restarts-after-2hrs\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  An Olympic men's football match between Argentina and Morocco had to be restarted after almost two hours following VAR drama.  The game had apparently ended 2-2 in Saint-Etienne.  Cristian Medina thought he had rescued a draw for Argentina in the 16th minute of added time.  There was a pitch invasion after the goal, but after a lengthy delay, Medina's goal was ruled out by VAR for offside.  The game lasted for three minutes after the restart before the referee blew the final whistle.  Morocco won the game 2-1.  I am very lucky - Morgan on signing contract with Chelsea  Ten Hag names 29-man squad for Man Utd's pre-season tour [Full list]  AFCON: CAF dividing Africa - Senegal's Gueye speaks on returning gold medals to Morocco  Moroccan club sack Senegal midfielder over AFCON 2025 title stripping remarks  'Senegal beat Morocco fair and square' - Rooney slams CAF over AFCON 2025 verdict  Senegal refuses to return AFCON trophy after CAF awards title to Morocco  AFCON: 'Corruption' - Senegal's Mane blasts CAF for awarding trophy to Morocco  AFCON 2025: 'Daylight robbery' - Shehu Sani slams CAF for declaring Morocco winner  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"